                        "section_title_1": "Abstract",
                        "section_title_2": "Background",
                        "iao_name_1": "textual abstract section",
                        "iao_id_1": "IAO:0000315"
                    },
                    "text": "The diagnosis of C. difficile infection (CDI) relies on using a nucleic acid amplification test (NAAT) followed by confirmatory toxin enzyme immunoassay (EIA). This study examined the utility of fecal biomarkers and C. difficile bacterial quantity (BQ) in differentiating patients with true infection (NAAT+/EIA+) from patients with colonization (NAAT+/EIA-) in the context of C. difficile ribotypes.",
                    "sentences": [],
                    "annotations": [
                        {
                            "text": "C. difficile",
